&lt;h2>Overview&lt;span class="hx-absolute -hx-mt-20" id="overview">&lt;/span>
&lt;a href="#overview" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section">&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;p>A plug-and-play solution to turn any &lt;strong>Raspberry Pi&lt;/strong> into a &lt;strong>full-screen media kiosk&lt;/strong> player. Automatically plays videos, PowerPoint presentations, PDFs and image slideshows from a USB stick or local storage — all rendered via &lt;strong>Chromium&lt;/strong>.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Ideal for installations, exhibitions, digital signage or any stage use case requiring automatic media playback.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2>Features&lt;span class="hx-absolute -hx-mt-20" id="features">&lt;/span>
&lt;a href="#features" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section">&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Autoplay on boot&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Supports: video, PDF, PowerPoint (converted), image slideshows&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Load from USB stick or local storage&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Chromium in kiosk mode (full-screen, no UI)&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Simple configuration&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h2>Requirements&lt;span class="hx-absolute -hx-mt-20" id="requirements">&lt;/span>
&lt;a href="#requirements" class="subheading-anchor" aria-label="Permalink for this section">&lt;/a>&lt;/h2>&lt;ul>
&lt;li>Raspberry Pi (any recent generation)&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Raspberry Pi OS&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Chromium (included by default on Raspberry Pi OS)&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
